cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI 

This paper deals with computer vision and neural networks, specifically for event-based cameras. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of spiking neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of self-supervised learning and deep learning techniques suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The application of the network for navigation purposes suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of hybrid neural networks suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
